    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-09-04T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-09-04T22:00:00-05:00" n="552"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d552">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13694: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jarvis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-09-05T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 5, 1936—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 5—11 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My August 23, 11 a.m.<note n="85" xml:id="d552fn85">Not printed.</note> The
                    Communists in southern Kansu are moving north through Changhsien, Lungsi and
                    Weiyuan districts. It is uncertain whether Minhsien is still infested. In
                    eastern Kansu the Communists are still based on Hwanhsien, and Yuwang in
                    Ningsia, but rove the countryside to within a short distance of Kuyuan.</p>
                <p>2. All Americans in Kansu (including West Kansu) have evacuated to Lanchow or
                    into Shensi except Miss Bertha Roberson at Taochow old city and Mr. James Vigna
                    at Siaho (both of Assemblies of God) and Mr. Earl Peterson, Miss Jennie Wedicson
                    and Miss Anna Madsen at Pingliang and Miss Edith Johnson at Kingchwan (all of
                    Scandinavian Alliance Mission); Marshal Chang Hsueh Liang’s<note n="86"
                        xml:id="d552fn86">Vice Commander in Chief, Bandit Suppression Forces for the
                        Northwest.</note> headquarters in Sian has sent special instructions to both
                    the Kansu Governor and the Kansu Pacification Commissioner to afford them
                    protection. The Lanchow-Pingliang-Sian motor road is again open. Sent to the
                    Department, Peiping, Nanking, Shanghai.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jarvis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
